modules.description: Provides message queue operations for sending and receiving messages, including creating, opening, closing, and removing queues. Works with message descriptors, message buffers, and priority values. Used to implement inter-process communication in Unix environments with precise control over message delivery.

Provides operations to open, send, receive, and manage POSIX message queues, including timed sends and receives, attribute manipulation, and queue deletion. Works with message queues identified by named paths, message data, and queue attributes specifying message size and capacity. Used for inter-process communication with priority-based message handling and timeout-controlled operations.
